title: Pakistan v England live scores: First Test, day five live blog, videos, highlights
text:
ALASTAIR Cook’s record-breaking double century left the first Test between Pakistan and England headed for a draw, but there’s still a faint chance a result could eventuate on day five in Abu Dhabi.
England went to stumps on day four on 8-569, holding a slender lead of 46 runs thanks to captain Cook’s remarkable innings.
The opener was dismissed for 263 after occupying the crease for 528 balls and 836 minutes, in the process becoming the third-longest innings (in terms of time) in the history of Test cricket.
He was expected to declare overnight but surprisingly sent tailenders Stuart Broad and Adil Rashid back in to bat at the start of day five.
